Hope and support from,

snippet.textDisplay: Rosanna, I am so, so sorry about Cookie. We all know how much you love her. It may not be any consolation, but you’re not alone. Several years ago I lost my first dog to an auto immune disease. He had swelling in his brain and spinal cord. He started losing mobility and vision. For the last months of his life he had open sores on his paws and shoulders, and by the last few hours is nose had started to bleed (he had a fungal infection in his nose). He spent three days at a veterinary university for a blood transfusion. Nothing worked. We ended up having to euthanize him, because that big guy still held on. That dog was my baby brother. I want you to remember that you did everything you could for Cookie. It’ll probably always hurt to talk about her. But you are strong. The only thing you need to do right now is take care of yourself. Grieve at your own pace. You have thousands of people that are here to support you. Don’t forget that. We’re here for you ❤️❤️❤️
